In order to use the formula above, we must first get the rates of return. To do this, we can solve for the change in market price by subtracting the new value from the old value, then adding this value to the dividend. Once we have the total, we can divide it by the old value.

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Rate of return}&=\dfrac{\text{Dividend}+(\text{New value}-\text{Old value})}{\text{Old value}}
\end{aligned}$$
